# =============================================================================
# nicheprohub.com — POST-CUTOVER REDIRECT-ONLY .htaccess
#
# DO NOT deploy this to burchcontracting.com. This file is meant to REPLACE
# whatever is currently in nicheprohub.com's docroot once the deploy workflow
# has been repointed to burchcontracting.com's hosting account and this
# repo's content is no longer being served from nicheprohub.com.
#
# What it does: every request to nicheprohub.com (any path, any query string)
# 301s to the identical path on https://burchcontracting.com. This is a pure
# domain-level passthrough — nicheprohub.com currently serves the exact same
# repo/content as burchcontracting.com will, so there is no legacy-URL
# mapping to do here (that work is in the main public/.htaccess, which
# handles the *old Next.js* burchcontracting.com's different URL structure).
#
# Deployment: replace the entire contents of nicheprohub.com's docroot
# .htaccess with this file (rename to .htaccess). It does not require any
# other files in the docroot to keep working — every request is redirected
# before any static-file lookup happens.
# =============================================================================

RewriteEngine On

# Redirect everything (any host: nicheprohub.com or www., any scheme) to the
# identical path on burchcontracting.com. QSA appends the original query
# string automatically (and omits it cleanly when there isn't one) — no
# separate www/https handling needed here since burchcontracting.com's own
# .htaccess normalizes those on arrival.
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://burchcontracting.com/$1 [R=301,L,QSA]
